<item>
 <title>Reflections on an enormous puddle</title>
 <link>http://quietlittlelies.com/article/reflections-enormous-puddle</link>
 <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-date field-field-date-published&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;span class=&quot;date-display-single&quot;&gt;25 Jul 2007&lt;/span&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-text field-field-summary&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;p&gt;Written after the floods in Yorkshire, then published during the major UK flooding in June/July 2007&lt;/p&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You ignored all the warnings&lt;br /&gt;
About global warming&lt;br /&gt;
(Or climate change as we now call it)&lt;br /&gt;
You dismissed the statistics&lt;br /&gt;
As myth told by mystics&lt;br /&gt;
In favour of cramming your wallit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All those air miles behind you&lt;br /&gt;
Expanding your mind? You&lt;br /&gt;
Know: brains aren’t things on which you sit.&lt;br /&gt;
So instead now you find&lt;br /&gt;
An expanded behind&lt;br /&gt;
That’s the size of the cloud you emit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, given the rain&lt;br /&gt;
Fell again, and again,&lt;br /&gt;
And poor Yorkshire is all under watter&lt;br /&gt;
Then if you still deny&lt;br /&gt;
The state of the sky&lt;br /&gt;
You must be as mad as a hatter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;But if you’re not sure&lt;br /&gt;
Of the need for a cure&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;field field-type-nodereference field-field-author&quot;&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;field-item odd&quot;&gt;
                    &lt;a href=&quot;/author/j-p-stacey&quot;&gt;J-P Stacey&lt;/a&gt;        &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
